	<p>ADDME</p>
	
	<definition>
	<title>ADDME</title>
	<statement>
		<p>The <term>angular momentum</term> of a rigid object about a given axis is the product of the object's moment of inertia and angular velocity about that axis: <me>\vec{L} = I\vec{\omega}</me></p>
	</statement>
</definition>

		<exercises>
	<title>Activities</title>
			<exercise>
			<title>Explanation - Distance and Intensity</title>
			  <p>Your friend measures the intensity of a sound wave to be <m>I</m>.  If you are twice as far away from the source of the wave as your friend, what will you measure the intensity to be?  Explain your reasoning.</p>
			</exercise>
